  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed; all credibility factor gaps are honestly documented with explicit confidence scores and wide uncertainty bounds where applicable. One factor (model inputs) carries an explicitly-flagged low-confidence epistemic gap that is fully justified and accepted as residual risk given corroborating experimental evidence. Decision: Accepted with documented rationale.",
